Oh yes, I see, I was able to reproduce that. Instead we could do:

```diff
         if (parse_transition_rule(&p, transitions[i])) {
-            PyErr_Format(PyExc_ValueError,
-                         "Malformed transition rule in TZ string: %R",
-                         tz_str_obj);
+            if (!PyErr_ExceptionMatches(PyExc_MemoryError)) {
+                PyErr_Format(PyExc_ValueError,
+                             "Malformed transition rule in TZ string: %R",
+                             tz_str_obj);
+            }
             goto error;
         }
     }
```

Since `{day,calendar}rule_new` (the subfunctions) only raise `ValueError`s.
